  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6771.47 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6770 (-11.5B) and max positive gamma at 6780 (+10.1B), dealers are likely covering short delta as we bounce off the 6770 amplifying level, creating buying pressure. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and will aggressively buy this dip while selling any push toward 6780, creating a tight 10-point trading range. Key inflection points are 6770 (major support where dealer buying accelerates) and the GEX flip at 6806 where the regime would shift to negative gamma if breached.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect strong support at 6770 with choppy action capped near 6780.",
